trans-unit.source: Represents the smallest and largest possible paragraph width that can fully contain the specified text content.
Determines whether the specified object is equal to the current <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.Object"></xref> to compare with the current <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> object.
`true` if obj is equal to the current object; otherwise, `false`.
If obj is not a object, `false` is returned.

Determines whether the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> is equal to the current <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> object.

The <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> to compare with the current <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> object.
`true` if value is equal to the current object; otherwise, `false`.
Serves as a hash function for <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref>.
It is suitable for use in hashing algorithms and data structures such as a hash table.
An <xref href="System.Int32"></xref> value that represents the hash code for the current object.
Gets the largest paragraph width possible that can fully contain the specified text content.
A <xref href="System.Double"></xref> that represents the largest paragraph width possible.
Gets the smallest paragraph width possible that can fully contain the specified text content.
The minimum paragraph width corresponds to the word that has the greatest width in the text content.
A <xref href="System.Double"></xref> that represents the smallest paragraph width possible.
Compare two <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> strings for equality.
The first instance of <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> to compare.
The second instance of <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> to compare.
`true` to show the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> objects are equal; otherwise, `false`.
Compare two <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> objects for inequality.

The objects are equal if their <xref:System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.MinMaxParagraphWidth.MinWidth%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.MinMaxParagraphWidth.MaxWidth%2A> properties are equal.
The first instance of <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> to compare.
The second instance of <xref href="System.Windows.Media.TextFormatting.CharacterBufferReference"></xref> to compare.
`false` to show left is equal to right; otherwise, `true`.
